caption: Great quality empanadas! One of my lunch options when I used to work downtown. Service is quick.
Literally the best thing I've ever put in my mouth.

I haven’t tried them all. But today I went into The French Market and I happened to come across this wonderful little gem!!! This was my first time getting something from here...but let me tell you, it WILL NOT be my last!!!! I had the beef and rice empanadas. Holy cow! Usually, I will take a picture to go along with a review but after bite #1, I demolished that thang!!! Soooo happy I stopped by. Will be back! I hope they have some of the other flavors I was interested in today on my next visit!! A plus plus guys!! And that mild sauce tho! I love that I can taste the heat but it still has flavor, I can taste the cilantro...which is one of my favorite flavors. I used the whole little cup on my 1 empanada. You have made me a whole fan today, Lito’s. Also, I see reviews about poor service and wrong orders but the lady that I spoke with was real nice and helpful. No complaint on the service.

Good empanadas but terrible service. I really need to stop giving them money. Regularly get incorrect items, or missing items, or missing sauce. If you order from them don't expect to get what you ordered.
My favorite is the spinach and mozzarella.
Some of the tastiest empanadas I've ever had!

I had a bad experience. The service was so rude, like I inconvenienced the lady at the counter because I wanted 16 empanadas. My order was so simple and I wasn't even being difficult but it was almost closing time, 5:55pm. She also claimed they were all out of sauces which is fine but her bad attitude made me feel like she just didn't want to deal with me. On top of that, she charged me full price per empanada despite the daily deal of 3 for $11. The difference wasn't worth the trouble. I've worked in the service industry a long time and I get that everyone has bad days but it's not okay to treat customers like an inconvenience. Customers are why we put on our aprons everyday. There are so many other places to choose from in the French Market with kind-hearted people that work hard to keep customers coming back. I regret my decision and I won't be returning here.

The empanadas are great - they're hot, fresh, and flavorful and don't skimp at all on what they're stuffed with - but the sauces are the absolute perfect companions for the empanadas they serve here. They're also pretty fairly priced, so you'll likely want to take advantage of their offer of three empanadas for a slight discount.
